Representative Mark Takai, who has served the people of Hawaii for over 20 years, is retiring. As a Lieutenant Colonel in the Hawaii Army National Guard, he has been a champion for military personnel, veterans, and working families. He has also been an advocate for cancer research, and President Obama commends him for his leadership, service, courage, and tireless advocacy. The President and First Lady extend their support and well wishes to Takai and his family as they face his battle with cancer.